{"type":"message","id":"ae9feeeb","parentId":"17780b7b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T23:10:27.023Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's thinking about moving from Tennessee to New York and is concerned about U-Haul costs. Let me give him some practical alternatives.\n","thinkingSignature":"1dca3d4c743d96b95325d936a9490520b548bef3891c2b60fc737799fc82dae6"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYeah U-Haul can get pricey, especially for cross-country. Here are cheaper options:\n\n**🚚 Truck Rental Alternatives:**\n- **Budget Truck** — often cheaper base rates, has student/military/AARP discounts\n- **Penske** — unlimited mileage on one-ways, good for long distance\n- **Enterprise** — wider truck selection, sometimes better deals\n\n**📦 Container/Ship Options:**\n- **U-Pack** — you pay for the space you use in a trailer/container, often cheaper than full truck\n- **PODS** — container delivered to your door, you load it\n- **Freight pods** — some companies ship by cubic foot\n\n**🚗 Car/Towing:**\n- **BringFido / car shipping** — if only car needs to move\n- ** tow behind** — if you have a car, tow it behind a rental truck\n\n**From Knoxville → NY is a long haul** — what's driving you up there? Just the two of you + stuff, or is this a full apartment move? That affects which option makes most sense. I can look up specific pricing if you tell me roughly how much stuff you're moving."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1396,"output":268,"cacheRead":56640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58304,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777417810767,"responseId":"064071534525dda292b8ebe9b648ba8d"}}
