      \"runtimeMs\": 196648,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": true,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"lastAccountId\": \"rex\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/agents/rex/sessions/52ceac30-064d-4e1c-9ce5-dafc89c67dab.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Good, now I have all the content for video 2. Let me now read the transcript and summary for video 3.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_f0vx9ummuz57_1\",\n              \"name\": \"read\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"path\": \"/tmp/transcript_3.txt\"\n              }\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_f0vx9ummuz57_2\",\n              \"name\": \"read\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"path\": \"/tmp/summary_3.txt\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n          \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 9123,\n            \"output\": 82,\n            \"totalTokens\": 54677,\n            \"cacheRead\": 45472,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1777386458498,\n          \"responseId\": \"063ff6da2cdd817a861e7d13be1865bf\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"a8d7bab8\",\n            \"seq\": 34\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:rex:subagent:60ee1346-39bf-4c3f-842f-4bf7bdec3d86\",\n      \"agentId\": \"rex\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:rex:telegram:direct:8212808444\",\n      \"label\": \"alex-finn-batch2\",\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-agent-rex-subagent-60ee1346-39bf-4c3f-842f-4bf7bdec3d86\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n        \"accountId\": \"rex\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1777386372258,\n      \"sessionId\": \"c8f54ad7-df77-4a3c-afb9-7a9156b0c3e8\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 38528,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1777385882562,\n      \"endedAt\": 1777386097970,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 93213,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": true,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"lastAccountId\": \"rex\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/agents/rex/sessions/c8f54ad7-df77-4a3c-afb9-7a9156b0c3e8.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"user\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\\n\\nBegin. Your assigned task is in the system prompt under **Your Role**; execute it to completion.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"timestamp\": 1777386129291,\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"d7187f99\",\n            \"seq\": 22\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Now I need to write the .md files for videos 2 and 3. Let me create those files.\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_z888qgsige84_1\",\n              \"name\": \"write\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"content\": \"# 5 OpenClaw use cases that will actually improve your life\\n- **Channel:** Alex Finn\\n- **Video Title:** 5 OpenClaw use cases that will actually improve your life\\n- **Video URL:** https://youtu.be/qRA0MyPlEPE\\n- **Date:** 2026-04-28\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Transcription\\n\\nOpenClaw is the single most powerful piece of software ever released. The problem is 99% of people have no idea how to get value out of it. In this video, I'll go over five use cases you can steal today to instantly start getting value out of OpenClaw. You will be obsessed with OpenClaw by the end of this video. So, let's lock in and get into it. The first use case I'm going to go over is the daily memory tracker. And this does two massive things. One, it greatly improves the memory of your OpenClaw. It makes it go from dumb to genius. But two, it gives you an incredible track record of everything you work on day in and day out. This allows you to track everything you've talked about, everything you've coded, everything you've built, everything you've shipped. It's like a journal for your working life that you don't have to manage or track yourself. It's all done automatically. So, I'm going to show you how it works, then I'll give you the prompt for it so you can build it yourself. My OpenClaw built this dashboard out for me for all our daily memories. By default, OpenClaw doesn't track daily memories. Now with this, it does. And now I can go back and any day, in any month, in any year, I can see what me and my OpenClaw discussed on that day. So, if I built an app a couple months ago and I forgot how it worked or I forgot how I built it, I can go all the way back to a specific day that I built it, click on that day, and now I can see the exact things I built and did on that day. I can see on this random day I clicked on January 27th, I built out the brains in the tools model, we re-implemented different models for different use cases inside OpenClaw, which saved a ton of money. And now I can see exactly how we built that out and what we discussed to build that out. And even the more impactful part about this is this now drives the entire memory system for my OpenClaw. Ever since I implemented this daily memory system, my OpenClaw has never forgot a thing. It remembers everything. I can say, \\\"Hey, remember that project we started 3 months ago? Let's resume it.\\\" And then now my OpenClaw can start working on it again. It did not do that before. So, you need to implement this daily memory system. It It allows you to track everything you do in intense detail and improves the memory of your OpenClaw by 10x. So, here's how you set it up. Let's go into Telegram and I'll give you the prompt down below as well that you can just copy and paste. I want to set up a daily memory system. We should have logs for every day we work together. Every discussion we have, you should put a summary into this daily tracker system. Then yo\n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\n recording video (VSL)\\n3. What you get breakdown\\n4. Before/after comparison\\n5. Testimonials — CRITICAL, buyers need social proof\\n6. Early-bird pricing + countdown\\n7. 30-day money-back guarantee\\n8. FAQ block (handles objections)\\n\\n---\\n\\n**BUDGET ESTIMATES:**\\n\\nFor meaningful multi-platform tests:\\n- Meta: $500-1000/month\\n- TikTok: $300-500/month\\n- Google: $200-400/month\\n- Reddit: $300-500/month\\nTotal: ~$1,500-2,500/month\\n\\nStart with Meta only if budget is tight. Scale to TikTok once you find what hooks.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**TOP 3 IMMEDIATE ACTIONS:**\\n\\n1. Build one-page sales site — even a Gumroad page with strong description works\\n2. Create one short demo video (5 min screen recording of OpenClaw doing something impressive) — this is your best ad creative\\n3. Launch Meta Advantage+ at $15-20/day targeting productivity/AI interests — see what CPL you get before scaling\\n\\n---\\n\\nThe positioning is strong — daily-user authenticity is the real differentiator. Urgency case is solid. Main question: budget and whether to test ads first or validate message organically on X first?\\n\\n— Rex 🔍📊\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n          \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 25308,\n            \"output\": 400,\n            \"totalTokens\": 45579,\n            \"cacheRead\": 19871,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1777345488477,\n          \"responseId\": \"063f56d056d7cb94adfb89d5c994fbd5\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"b10e2a3f\",\n            \"seq\": 42\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"I've completed the research and sent all findings to Bobby on Telegram. Let me summarize what I did.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Done. Here's what I accomplished:\\n\\n**Research completed across all 6 areas:**\\n1. **Target audience** — Solopreneurs, busy professionals, tech early adopters, side-hustlers. Pain points: not knowing where to start, AI requiring constant prompting, wasting time on manual tasks.\\n\\n2. **Product positioning** — Hook: \\\"Your AI answers questions. Mine works 24/7.\\\" Promise: turn OpenClaw into your personal AI employee. Dark navy + gold = premium, authentic, real-world.\\n\\n3. **Urgency** — Agentic AI is the 2025-2026 wave (Gartner: early adopters get 3x faster results). Early mover window closing fast — free tutorials will flood in within months.\\n\\n4. **Why OpenClaw vs ChatGPT** — ChatGPT is an assistant you manage. OpenClaw is an employee you delegate to. 24/7, proactive, connects to your apps.\\n\\n5. **Easy start** — Before/after day one comparison. 2-hour setup hook. Screen recording GIF showing the process.\\n\\n6. **Ads strategy** — Meta #1 (CPL ~$22 avg, CPC $0.30-4), TikTok #2 (cheaper, AI content performs well), Google Search (high intent), Reddit (warm niche communities). Funnel: Cold ad → one-page sales site → checkout. Budget: $1,500-2,500/month for multi-platform tests.\\n\\nSent to Bobby in 8 Telegram messages (had to break it up due to Telegram's character limit).\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n          \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 25750,\n            \"output\": 347,\n            \"totalTokens\": 45968,\n            \"cacheRead\": 19871,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1777345499131,\n          \"responseId\": \"063f56dba01fb0c27f8a373f77492daf\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"aad6591d\",\n            \"seq\": 44\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}[... 54561 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["count","sessions"],"sessions":[{"sessionId":"36a323f2-04c1-4cb8-a4d5-d253f531f78a","status":"done","startedAt":1777423318016,"endedAt":1777423342945,"runtimeMs":24929},{"sessionId":"52ceac30-064d-4e1c-9ce5-dafc89c67dab","status":"done","startedAt":1777386381593,"endedAt":1777386583421,"runtimeMs":196648},{"sessionId":"c8f54ad7-df77-4a3c-afb9-7a9156b0c3e8","status":"done","startedAt":1777385882562,"endedAt":1777386097970,"runtimeMs":93213},{"sessionId":"6f0886a5-87bc-451a-a92e-2385f79112fe","status":"done","startedAt":1777385902743,"endedAt":1777386310917,"runtimeMs":308185}