{"type":"message","id":"91f3b845","parentId":"39d00890","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:43:23.248Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Rex has been trying to reach me but messages aren't coming through to my main session. Looking at the last message from Rex's session, Rex was telling Bobby \"I've sent Dean two messages and I'm checking his inbox but nothing's come through yet.\"\n\nThis is a cross-agent communication issue. Rex is trying to message me (Dean/main) but the messages aren't reaching my inbox. This is likely because:\n\n1. Rex is a sub-agent with its own session\n2. The messages are being sent to the wrong session or not being routed properly\n3. The Telegram delivery might be going to the wrong account\n\nLooking at the session details - Rex's Telegram is set up as `telegram:g-agent-rex-telegram-direct-8212808444`. When Rex tries to message Bobby, it sends from its own Telegram bot account. \n\nThe problem might be that when Rex tries to reach me, it's either sending to the wrong account entirely or the cross-agent communication flow between Rex's bot and my main session isn't properly connected. I need to look at the agent configuration to see how they're supposed to be communicating.","thinkingSignature":"c1530bfdb4d68f677154aa53886c6ae70e6e9f0ebfcbcb30b0b632aa0d9694d7"},{"type":"text","text":"Looking at Rex's session — he was trying to reach me directly. It looks like the messages weren't getting through. This is likely because Rex is a separate agent on a different Telegram bot account, and when he tries to message me (Dean) it goes to a different inbox rather than my main session.\n\nLet me check how agents are supposed to communicate:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c2oyeusvvbu5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/rex/agent.json 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49604,"output":340,"cache