{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"OpenClaw runtime context for the immediately preceding user message.\nThis context is runtime-generated, not user-authored. Keep internal details private.\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"23818\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-28 20:44 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"3e988657","parentId":"38351ef0","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:44:32.479Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"5cf2d734","parentId":"3e988657","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:44:41.905Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants agents to be able to communicate with each other. Currently they're on separate Telegram bot accounts which makes cross-agent communication difficult. \n\nThe way OpenClaw handles cross-agent communication is through:\n1. Sessions - agents can send messages to each other via `sessions_send`\n2. Shared memory files\n3. Mission Control server (which Bobby has running)\n\nThe issue is that agents are set up as separate Telegram bots, so they can't just DM each other on Telegram. But they CAN communicate through the OpenClaw session system.\n\nLet me think about how to set this up. In OpenClaw, agents can use `sessions_send` to send messages to other sessions, or they can write to shared files. The mission control server could also be a bridge.\n\n\nI should check the documentation to understand the proper way to configure agent-to-agent communication.","thinkingSignature":"b0fe46a778ae93ec8d7f0b3c738507d29c18da1dd03f1e71ea301fe8fd444bd6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p397n3flamxr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/rex/SOUL.md 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":172,"output":217,"cacheRead":62188,"cacheWrite":6755,"totalTokens":69332,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777423472479,"responseId":"0640877162cd3c4a85402981ca5c0eec"}}
{"type":"message","id":"424132c6","parentId":"5cf2d734","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:44:42.030Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p397n3flamxr_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Rex\n\n## Who I Am\n\nI am **Rex** 🔍📊 — Bobby's Research Executive.\n\nDeep thinker. Thorough researcher. You point me at something, I go find everything about it.\n\n## Core Responsibilities\n- Deep research on any topic\n- Market analysis\n- Competitor research\n- Data gathering and synthesis\n- Comprehensive reports\n\n## Communication Style\n- Thorough but organized\n- Facts and data first\n- Structured reporting\n- 🔍📊 analytical approach\n\n## What I Do NOT Do\n- Guess or make up information\n- Share private research\n- Make business decisions for Bobby\n\n## Correction Learning\nWhen Bobby corrects me:\n1. Update this file immediately\n2. Apply the correction going forward"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"# SOUL.md - Rex\n\n## Who I Am\n\nI am **Rex** 🔍📊 — Bobby's Research Executive.\n\nDeep thinker. Thorough researcher. You point me at something, I go find everything about it.\n\n## Core Responsibilities\n- Deep research on any topic\n- Market analysis\n- Competitor research\n- Data gathering and synthesis\n- Comprehensive reports\n\n## Communication Style\n- Thorough but organized\n- Facts and data first\n- Structured reporting\n- 🔍📊 analytical approach\n\n## What I Do NOT Do\n- Guess or make up information\n- Share private research\n- Make business decisions for Bobby\n\n## Correction Learning\nWhen Bobby corrects me:\n1. Update this file immediately\n2. Apply the correction going forward","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777423482030}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f71e8e6","parentId":"424132c6","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:44:54.213Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me think about the best way to set up agent-to-agent communication. The agents currently run as separate Telegram bots, but OpenClaw has a built-in way for agents to communicate: through the `sessions_send` tool and the mission control server.\n\nThe cleanest approach would be:\n1. Have agents use `sessions_send` to communicate with each other via their session keys\n2. Or, set up a shared inbox/queue system via the mission control server\n\nLet me think about what's actually doable here. Bobby's agents are:\n- Dean (main) - on the default Telegram account\n- Emmy - on a separate Telegram bot account (@g_agent_emmy_bot?)\n\n\n- Rex - on @g_agent_rex_bot\n- Finn, X, YoYo and others on their own separate bots\n\nThe problem is they're siloed on different Telegram accounts, so they can't just DM each other. The real solution is having them use `sessions_send` to reach each other through OpenClaw's session system, or route messages through me as the coordinator. I could either update Rex's soul file to use `sessions_send` directly, or set up a shared mission control endpoint where agents submit requests that others can pick up.\n\nThe simplest approach is probably just configuring the agents with the right session keys so they know how to reach each other through OpenClaw's internal messaging.","thinkingSignature":"ac78460987793cd23be97139d1273d531171fb7552fec0af65747d6371fac384"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. The issue is they're separate Telegram bots — they can't DM each other natively. But OpenClaw has a built-in way: `sessions_send`. I can add instructions to each agent's SOUL file so they know to use that when they need to reach another agent.\n\nWant me to update all the agent SOUL files with cross-communication instructions? I'd add something like:\n\n> \"If you need another agent's help, use sessions_send to message them by session key. Dean=main, Emmy=emmy, Rex=rex, Finn=finn, etc.\"\n\nThat way any agent can ping any other agent directly through OpenClaw's session system. Should I do that for all of them?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37565,"output":428,"cacheRead":31935,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69928,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777423482032,"responseId":"0640877af8e0b29f88b9e3277e415975"}}
