{"type":"message","id":"64ecf61c","parentId":"da0fb81e","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:45:59.657Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, so the agents are: cody, dj, emmy, finn, main, reese, rex, tt, x, yoyos. \"main\" is me (Dean). I need to add the cross-communication instruction to all the other agents' SOUL.md files.\n\nLet me update each one. I'll append a \"Cross-Agent Communication\" section to each SOUL.md.","thinkingSignature":"9dea92a0166efe652a7a247838711fa9d4b66fbc0149b63160c574c8cc90cf0e"},{"type":"text","text":"Got 10 agents. Updating all their SOUL files now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_503pch90fmyi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"for agent in cody dj emmy finn rex reese tt x yoyos; do\n  cat >> ~/.openclaw/agents/$agent/SOUL.md << 'EOF'\n\n## Cross-Agent Communication\nTo message another agent directly, use sessions_send with their session key:\n- Dean (main): agent:main:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- Emmy: agent:emmy:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- Finn: agent:finn:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- Rex: agent:rex:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- Cody: agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- DJ: agent:dj:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- YoYo: agent:yoyos:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- Reese: agent:reese:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- X (Agent X): agent:x:telegram:direct:8212808444\n- TT: agent:tt:telegram:direct:8212808444\n\nWhen you need another agent's help, send them a message via sessions_send. They will respond and the conversation continues from there.\nEOF\n  echo \"Updated $agent\"\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37810,"output":381,"cacheRead":31935,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70126,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777423550155,"responseId":"064087be42d4503dff71593c6a7b8e30"}}
