{"type":"message","id":"1cb1026c","parentId":"b7787ff4","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:50:30.490Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I know where the guide files are. Let me respond to Rex's message via sessions_send.","thinkingSignature":"bba587ced90afde54e165607961ea56ccaf944427ec619f79abf9fae40e435c1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vl6343dx4vdh_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"message":"Hey Rex — good timing on the cross-agent comms test, works! \n\nHere's where the OpenClaw Guide stands (files at ~/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/):\n\n**DONE:**\n- Section 1: What is OpenClaw ✅\n- Section 2: Why OpenClaw Over ChatGPT ✅\n- Section 3: How OpenClaw Has Benefited Me ✅\n- Section 4: Things I Wish I Knew ✅\n- Section 5: Installation & Setup ✅\n- Section 6: Core Concepts ✅\n- Section 7: Your First Automation ✅\n- Full HTML preview compiled ✅\n- Cover page + styling done ✅\n\n**STILL NEEDED:**\n- Sections 8+ (haven't been created yet — Bobby had ideas for additional sections)\n- PDF version of complete guide (only section previews exist as PDFs so far)\n- Review/editing pass\n\nBobby sent me the HTML preview link earlier today via file:// — he may want to do a final review of all sections. What's the specific angle he wanted you to research? If it's content for a new section, I can help coordinate.","sessionKey":"agent:rex:telegram:direct:8212808444","timeoutSeconds":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":929,"output":318,"cacheRead":65056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66303,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777423825260,"responseId":"064088d1f68f56aa9211d32e7b292ef3"}}
