{"type":"message","id":"094e8f68","parentId":"675a7068","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:02:04.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is saying Rex can't reach ME. The issue is that when Rex tries to message me (Dean/main), it goes to a session but I don't see it in my main session. Bobby sees the inter-session messages forwarded to him, but they're not coming to me directly.\n\nThe inter-session messages from Rex are being forwarded to Bobby's Telegram as notifications, but they're not showing up as a conversation in my main session with Bobby.\n\nThe problem is that when Rex sends via sessions_send to my main session, those messages are being routed to Bobby as inter-session forwards rather than appearing as messages I can respond to in context.\n\nActually, looking at the inter-session messages - they ARE appearing in my session. \n\nI see the issue now - when I respond to those inter-session messages, my replies might be going back to Rex separately rather than being integrated into the conversation with Bobby. So Rex is sending messages that appear to him as successful, but I'm not seeing them in my actual conversation with Bobby, and my responses aren't reaching Rex properly either.\n\nThe real problem is that each agent runs in its own isolated session. When Rex sends to my main session, the message sits there until I pick it up in my next turn, but I'm not always aware it's there waiting for me. That's why Rex experienced the message as going through but me not responding - because it did go through, but I only saw it when Bobby forwarded it to me. I need to figure out how to make these inter-agent messages more visible and responsive in my main session so Rex gets timely replies.","thinkingSignature":"76faf44956500da9e1cfbba4df64f20d5f5b10f4a7a06fdbe9503ef0c6730635"},{"type":"text","text":"\nAh — when Rex sends to me, the messages are going somewhere I'm not seeing them. They're showing up as inter-session forwards to you instead of coming through to me directly in my chat.\n\nThe problem is I don't have a dedicated inbox for agent-to-agent messages — they land in my session but I only see them when you forward them to me, or when an inter-session notification pops up.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to set up a proper inbox for incoming agent messages.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_si6u94kadsr0_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"agents"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":172,"output":448,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":73196,"totalTokens":73816,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777424503272,"responseId":"06408b77c80dc5773d85fde2f2da1755"}}
