{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"OpenClaw runtime context for the immediately preceding user message.\nThis context is runtime-generated, not user-authored. Keep internal details private.\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"23829\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-28 21:23 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"bf5b9945","parentId":"d7930a6b","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:23:31.716Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"fc3fccf5","parentId":"bf5b9945","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:23:54.682Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants agents to be able to communicate directly and seamlessly, where when Rex messages Dean, it shows up naturally in Bobby's chat with Dean like a normal conversation. \n\nThe issue is that when agents message each other via sessions_send, those messages go to the agent's internal session queue but don't appear in the Telegram DM conversation that Bobby has with that agent.\n\nThere are a few possible approaches:\n\n1. **Webhook delivery** - When Rex sends to me via sessions_send, if the delivery mode is set to \"announce\" it should post to Telegram\n2. **All agents on same Telegram bot** - If all agents used the same Telegram bot/account, they'd all be in the same DM thread with Bobby\n\n\n3. **Heartbeat monitoring** - I could monitor for incoming agent messages and relay them to Bobby, but that's adding complexity\n4. **Check for Telegram channel config** - The cleanest fix might be setting up all agents to deliver to the same Telegram channel so messages land in one place\n\nThe real issue seems to be that when Rex sends a message to me, it arrives as a silent notification rather than appearing as a natural reply in our conversation. I'm wondering if there's a way to configure sessions_send to deliver directly to Telegram when the target session is active.\n\nThe `announce` delivery mode should send a Telegram message, but it's not working as expected. I'm also realizing that Bobby's interacting with different agents through different Telegram bots - his DM with Rex is through one bot account, and his DM with me is through another. So when Rex tries to reach me, the message gets queued internally rather than posted to our shared Telegram conversation. The core problem is that these separate bot accounts don't share a common chat thread with Bobby.\n\nI'm considering a few approaches: setting up a dedicated Telegram group where all agents are members so they can message to the same thread, routing everything through Bobby's main bot account, or creating a \"dispatcher\" workflow where agents send results back to Bobby directly rather than trying to communicate with each other. The group approach seems most promising, though it would require configuring the Telegram channels for each agent to use a shared group rather than separate DMs.","thinkingSignature":"fd2bb452e19f1f3d1471fe064913c55dc89345570ae9b7847b29416d3b9de031"},{"type":"text","text":"The issue is agents are on **separate Telegram bots** — Rex's messages to me go to a different DM thread than ours. Bobby sees them as system notifications, not as replies in our chat.\n\n**Fix options:**\n\n**Option 1: Group Chat (recommended)**\nCreate a Telegram group, add all agent bots to it, and have agents message that group. Everyone shares the same thread. Bobby can observe or participate.\n\n**Option 2: Same Telegram Bot**\nAll agents use the same bot account — then they're all in the same DM thread with Bobby. Most seamless but requires reconfiguring the agent accounts.\n\n**Option 3: Relay through me**\nI act as the hub. Rex sends findings to me → I relay to you with context. Works now, no config changes, but adds me as middleman.\n\n**Option 4: All agents DM Bobby directly**\nAgents just message Bobby on their own Telegram when they have results, rather than trying to reach each other.\n\nWhich would you prefer? Option 1 (group chat) is probably the cleanest for team coordination."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":172,"output":664,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":78029,"totalTokens":78865,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777425811716,"responseId":"0640909438a462c2f6d7615f39acb002"}}
