{"type":"message","id":"f85252a7","parentId":"f1ad7830","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:25:48.408Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants it to work so that when he tells Agent A to ask Agent B something, Agent A can message Agent B and the conversation flows naturally without needing manual relays.\n\nThe issue is the separate Telegram bots. The cleanest solution that matches what Bobby wants would be having all agents use the same Telegram bot/account, so they all share the same conversation thread with Bobby.\n\nLet me think about this - if all agents use the same Telegram bot (same bot token, same account), then:\n- Bobby DMs the bot\n- The bot routes to the correct agent based on the message\n- Agent A can message Agent B through the same bot session\n- Everything is in one thread\n\n\n- I'd need to reconfigure all the agents to use a single Telegram bot account instead of separate ones, which would require updating the bindings and channel configurations in the OpenClaw setup. This is definitely doable, but it's a bigger architectural change than the other options.","thinkingSignature":"7d5876d93656fb045020982f28ab1409ae697fdabb67f65015e6264b95ae4084"},{"type":"text","text":"That means Option 2 — all agents on the **same Telegram bot**. Then:\n\n- You message one bot (@the same bot for everyone)\n- OpenClaw routes to the right agent based on context\n- Agent A can message Agent B in the same thread\n- Everything in one DM chain with you\n\nIt's a bigger config change — I'd need to consolidate all agents to use the same Telegram bot account. The other bots (@g_agent_rex_bot, @g_agent_emmy_bot, etc.) would become inactive.\n\nIt's doable. Want me to look into what it would take to set that up?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":172,"output":318,"cacheRead":77880,"cacheWrite":540,"totalTokens":78910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"tot