{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"OpenClaw runtime context for the immediately preceding user message.\nThis context is runtime-generated, not user-authored. Keep internal details private.\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"23833\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-28 21:33 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"a4542675","parentId":"8b8a880b","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:33:18.733Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"719b62f2","parentId":"a4542675","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:33:44.730Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's asking a good question. Why CAN'T all agents reach each other like I (Dean) can reach everyone?\n\nThe answer is: I AM reaching them via `sessions_send` — that works. When I send a message to Rex, he gets it. When Rex sends to me, I get it (it's just queued).\n\nThe REAL issue isn't reachability — it's that the messages go to different places:\n- Dean (main agent) has his own session that Bobby talks to directly\n- Rex has his own session on a different Telegram bot\n- When Rex sends to Dean, Bobby sees it as a system notification/forward, not as a message in our main chat\n\nSo technically they CAN reach each other. \n\nBut Bobby wants Rex's messages to show up as actual messages in our chat thread, not as notifications from another bot. The problem is that when Rex sends to Dean, it arrives in Dean's session — but since I'm already running in my main session, those messages queue up silently and Bobby sees them as inter-session notifications. What Bobby actually wants is for Rex to message him directly on Telegram so he sees it in his main chat with Rex, then loop me in if needed. That's really the cleanest solution.\n\nThe issue is that Bobby wants Rex to be able to reach ME (Dean) directly through Telegram DMs, not through OpenClaw's internal session system. When he says \"like you reach everyone,\" he means through normal Telegram messaging. But OpenClaw agents on separate Telegram bots can't actually DM each other — that's a Telegram limitation, not an OpenClaw one. I'm realizing the distinction here — Bobby wants Rex to message him directly on Telegram like a real person would, not through some inter-session notification system. I can make that happen by having Rex use the message tool to send a Telegram message to Bobby's chat ID, which gets him a real DM on the Telegram app. The real constraint is that agent-to-agent communication happens through session messaging, not native Telegram DMs, so Bobby needs to decide if he wants Rex messaging him directly or if the current session-based system is sufficient.","thinkingSignature":"c7b73ec535cb74825fa5d2afd04c47a0d546fd6244bbd70cadf10ae90bd2301b"},{"type":"text","text":"That's a fair question. The real answer:\n\n**I can reach them through OpenClaw's session system** (`sessions_send`) — and that works. Rex got my message and replied. But that's internal, not a real Telegram DM.\n\n**The limitation is Telegram itself.** Two bot accounts can't DM each other on Telegram — that's a Telegram rule, not an OpenClaw limitation. Every agent is on a separate bot (@g_agent_rex_bot, @g_agent_emmy_bot, etc.), and bots can't start conversations with each other.\n\n**What I CAN do:** I can update Rex's instructions so that when he has findings, he sends them directly to YOUR Telegram as a real message — not trying to reach me internally, just texting you directly. You'd get a real DM from Rex's bot.\n\nThat gives you direct access to Rex on Telegram. Is that closer to what you want?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":172,"output":613,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":78715,"totalTokens":79500,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777426398733,"responseId":"064092dff247fcb82f45fcebf90d4a2b"}}
